To Elizabeth Warren: Politics, scientific optimism, and compassion
--
You said on an interview with Ezra Klein recently that you did think fighting was the right metaphor for politics.

People are the same. Most people (maybe everyone?) appear to believe what they say they believe. In the short our differences of beliefs might have to be a fight, but in the long term we can change each others' beliefs.

Humans today operate under a lot of stress. Schools reward us for wide-ranging abstract thinking, but the economy rewards very focused, narrow thinking.

